<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-11-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="390" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                    <head>No. 1103.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Straus</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-11-21"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 21,
                            1888</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 159.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have much satisfaction in acknowledging Mr.
                        King’s dispatch, No. 133, of the 3d instant, reporting that His Imperial
                        Majesty the Sultan had decided to grant an iradeh to the representatives of
                        the University of Pennsylvania permitting archaeological explorations in
                        Assyria and Babylonia.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>